"explanation": "The defendant's actions constitute a significant breach of fiduciary duty and professional trust. In determining the sentence, the court considers the amount embezzled and the deliberate nature of the crime. However, several mitigating factors are present: the defendant has no prior criminal history and has demonstrated a degree of remorse and responsibility by initiating partial restitution. The outburst by the courtroom spectator has no legal bearing on this sentencing and was disregarded. A period of 6 months of incarceration is deemed appropriate to serve as a deterrent and punishment, balanced against the defendant's clean record and efforts to make the victim whole.",
